<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>RESPONSE TO THE JOINT COMMITTEE ON THE DRAFT DEREGULATION BILL CALL FOR EVIDENCE</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Acro</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Arco is the UK’s leading health and safety equipment distributor. The company is steeped in occupational health and safety, providing expert advice and safety solutions through its regional sales offices, on-site centres and forty-two strong trade counter network to 110,000 customers across the UK and internationally. This presence is supported </span><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">by </span></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">its in-house training and consultancy division which also provides other services such as project support, site surveys and other specialist services. Arco is committed to the future of the business and its customers, and therefore invests heavily in product innovation, its supply chain, distribution network, the communities in which the company operates and its people. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Arco is the expert in its field with 125 years’ experience in health and safety, and the business is driven by its purpose to keep people safe at work. Arco already has a number of connections with the Health and Safety Executive and knows its work well. The business is, for example, directly involved with the HSE’s Construction Dust Partnership Team (which works to raise awareness of hazardous dusts within the construction industry) and has in the past participated in Expert Groups on hearing and slips, trips and falls.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Given Arco’s expertise in the health and safety industry, this submission will focus on the aspects of the draft Bill that focus on health and safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Executive summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This response outlines Arco’s response to the Joint Committee on the Draft Deregulation Bill, Call for Evidence. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The organisation provides answers to the questions outlined in the consultation paper below which focus around the following parts of the draft Bill:</span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">exempting health &amp; safety rules for self-employed workers in low risk occupations; </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">putting a deregulatory ‘growth duty’ on non-economic regulators; and</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">removing</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> employment tribunal judges’ power to issue wide recommendations to businesses brought before them.</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Although Arco understands the government’s desire to reduce the regulatory burden placed on businesses, the business has concerns that the proposals on health and safety legislation and employee rights will have perverse consequences for employees. Arco’s response outlines areas in which the business would like the government to give further thought to before scrapping, and instead make use of initiatives and reforms already  underway such as the Red Tape Challenge and Professor </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt’s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> recommendations. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The draft Bill covers a broad range of legislation. Could the same results have been achieved using existing secondary legislation?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The 1974 Health and Safety at Work etc. Act heralded a revolution in health and safety in Britain. The results have been staggering with significant improvements delivered all round. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Britain as a result has an enviable reputation worldwide as a leader in health and safety:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 102.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">number of fatal injuries to employees have</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> fallen by 83%.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 102.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Non-fatal injuries have fallen by 77%. </span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 102.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Britain has the lowest rate of fatal injuries in the EU. </span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This record needs to be protected and enhanced; not endangered. The proposals outlined in this review, which seek to exempt self-employed workers from health and safety legislation and remove employment tribunal judges’ powers to issue recommendations to businesses brought before them, could both severely damage the protection of workers and their rights in the workplace. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">In 2011, the government began a review of health and safety, chaired by Professor </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Ragnar</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. His findings were published in November 2011 which included recommendations on how to reduce regulatory requirements on businesses, and remove pressures on business to go beyond what the regulations required. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> published an update report on progress made on implementing his recommendations in February 2013 which found that many of his proposals to tackle the</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">health and safety legislation had already been put into place, adding that he saw evidence that attitudes towards health and safety were changing. He did however state that </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">health and safety stakeholders need to engage further with their European counterparts. It is worth noting that the European Commission is currently undergoing a major review of health and safety legislation which is expected to be completed by 2015.  There were concerns raised by some regarding his report, who disagreed with several of his recommendations. Concerns were raised about one of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt’s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> proposals, which </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">was</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> to exempt self-employed workers from health and safety law, ‘where their activities pose no potential risk of harm to others.’ His consultation document clarified which categories of self-employed workers would and would not be affected by the exemption.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The above demonstrates that the proposals on exempting health and safety legislation for those perceived to be in low-risk occupations have raised concern amongst various stakeholders. Arco is concerned that the draft Deregulation Bill has not taken into account the recommendations given by Professor </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> on who should and should not, be included by this legislation. Arco is also concerned as to how the decision will be made about who are deemed to be in low-risk professions and whether or not ‘others’ are being put at risk. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Consideration should also be given to the Red Tape Challenge, a Cabinet Office led initiative, of which the second wave is taking place at the moment. The Red Tape Challenge could be used as a vehicle for reforms instead of introducing further regulatory burdens through additional legislation.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The points outlined above demonstrate that existing measures, already underway, should be used and given time to be implemented, without reforms through additional legislation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Are the changes in the draft Bill evidence-based and have any associated risks been properly taken into account?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.2pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The proposals on exemptions to health and safety legislation outlined in the draft Deregulation Bill do not take into account the benefits which health and safety legislation can bring to businesses. Instead, it is considered as a regulatory burden which should be removed. Arco believes consideration should be given to what impact the removal of health and safety legislation, as proposed under the draft Bill, may have on businesses and the self-employed, something which the HSE has done</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. They found that: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.4pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">27 million days were lost in 2012 on account of health and safety incidents. 27 million days that could have been refocused on productive activity.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.4pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The most frequent causes of injury according to HSE research are manual handling, slips, trips, and falls from height – all basic incidents which are preventable with simple precautions. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 62.4pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The total cost according to HSE estimates is £13.4 billion per year.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The above demonstrates the significant costs which businesses, including self-employed people, can incur when precautionary measures in health and safety legislation are not implemented effectively. Regulations such as those proposed by the draft Bill focus too hastily on what regulations can be removed, without considering the potential costs which can be incurred through injury and the personal impact of injuries. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Self-employed workers are more likely to turn to the state for support when they incur injuries, as it is unlikely that they would receive sick pay to cover their period of absence. This results in not just increased costs to self-employed workers when they are injured, but also leads to increased financial pressures on the welfare budget which will support them whilst they are out of work.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Arco is also concerned about proposals to put a deregulatory ‘growth duty’ on non-economic regulators and that this would result in them placing more emphasis on achieving this growth duty, than through offering protection. Arco undertakes joint-work with the HSE, and given the tight budget constraints, would not want the HSE’s focus diverted away from keeping people safe at work. Arco understands the concerns </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">raised</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> about increasing the knowledge base of regulators for the businesses the HSE regulates and the need for the body to provide clear, consistent advice, however Arco thinks the primary consideration for regulators, such as the HSE, is to offer protection to workers. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent does the draft Bill benefit consumers as well as businesses?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Reducing unnecessary regulation through the Red Tape Challenge has been a key focus for the government. The British Chambers of Commerce, for example, has estimated that health and safety red tape costs businesses £374million a year. However, investing in health and safety benefits workers, as well as protecting </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">businesses. Further research found that Risk Management and Benefit is good for employees, business and for a company’s short and long term sustainability.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Arco’s market research shows that all customers are facing recessionary pressure on budgets; customers are trying to reduce costs by rationalising both products specified and suppliers. There has been a large growth in ‘value’ health and safety equipment over the last 18 months and this trend has been particularly prevalent in the SME market. As customers turn towards value products as part of an effort to reduce their overheads, Arco believes that in doing so, customers need to remain vigilant in their personal care and do not compromise on their health and safety in the process. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Such trends all emphasise the need for ongoing education and awareness-raising – something the HSE is meant to undertake but lacks the resources and tools to do so effectively. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This evidence, collected from Arco’s customer base demonstrates the proposals to exempt self-employed workers from health and safety legislation, many of whom are represented in Arco’s customer base, do not benefit consumers, or businesses, although it may appear that way in the short-term. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We are concerned that the proposals to exempt self-employed workers may have a negative impact. For example, a self-employed person who requires personal protective equipment (PPE) in order to carry out their work safely may choose not to buy this equipment if it is not a legal requirement. Should they be injured at work as a result of this, it is likely that their injuries will be more severe and the costs they incur as a result of the accident, due to being unable to work, will be higher. The draft Bill states that it will exempt those self-employed persons who have no employees, and whose activities pose no potential risk to others, however it does not consider the potential harm that a self-employed person could incur whilst at work. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How does the provision in the draft Bill affect protections afforded to individuals under human rights and equalities legislation?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The draft Deregulation Bill contains provisions to remove the power for employment tribunals to make wider recommendations in successful discrimination cases, under the Equality Act 2010. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This may be perceived by some as the removal of a regulatory burden for employers. However, it endangers the rights of employees who look to tribunals to make independent and impartial decisions on their behalf. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">If tribunals are unable to make wider recommendations, fewer employees may choose to take their case to a tribunal. Even if employees have a case for a tribunal, they may not see the point in doing so if the tribunals now have fewer powers to make recommendations to employers. Although the above proposals may reduce the regulatory burden for employers, it decreases the rights of employees, and their ability to voice any complaints independently.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Will any or all of the proposals have any significant economic or financial impact? Do you have any evidence of the impact that will aid the Committee in their scrutiny?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Arco believes that health and safety is vital for economic competitiveness and the business has concerns from research of its customer base that as many businesses and self-employed workers face tight budgets, they are compromising on the PPE needed in their work. For many, buying value products seems like a ‘quick-fix’ solution to keeping costs low, however this is often a false economy as these products, although of good quality, do not generally have the same life expectancy. Should self-employed workers then have health and safety legislation governing their practices scrapped, there is a distinct risk that they will choose not to purchase equipment which protects their health and safety.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The points we have raised only consider the problems that a reduction in regulation could have in the short-term, however some industrial diseases, such as </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">mesothelioma</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> do not start to show symptoms until later in life. The industry is only now starting to see the true scale of the health problems resulting from a lack of protection for those working with asbestos and the concomitant impact this has on health services and the NHS.  Precautionary measures to prevent health problems such as </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">mesothelioma</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and industrial diseases caused by the inhalation of dust such as</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">pneumoconiosis can be prevented through simple steps such as wearing a face mask. This corresponds to points raised in Professor </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Löfstedt’s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> findings that risk-based systems help businesses comply with their duties and ensure that employees are protected. The need for risk-assessment amongst employees is paramount but should not become an unnecessary burden. These precautionary measures, which could potentially prevent future illnesses, would be put at risk if this legislation were to be enacted under the Bill.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The long-term impact of this removal of legislation would also have future economic effects. Long-term occupational illnesses will result in increased costs and pressures on the NHS in the future. With a health service which is set to struggle as people are living longer, and working further into old-age, the costs to the NHS are rising. Should self-employed workers become exempt from this legislation, this could lead to a new health crisis in the future from those who have not taken simple health and safety precautions as a result of this legislation.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/statistics/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hse.gov.uk/statistics/</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></p></body></html>